body:
We observed more scenarios that users still wanna put a transformer function after unnest.
E.g. assume a column has an array object: 
```
{
    "jsonColumn" : [
        {"data":{"a":"1","b":"2"},"timestamp":1719390721},
        {"data":{"a":"2","b":"4"},"timestamp":1719390722}
    ]
}
```

Before, the unnest result will be two rows: 
```
{
    "jsonColumn.timestamp": 1719390721,
    "jsonColumn.data.a": 1,
    "jsonColumn.data.b": 2,
},
{
    "jsonColumn.timestamp": 1719390722,
    "jsonColumn.data.a": 2,
    "jsonColumn.data.b": 4,
}
```

Now the parsed results will be: 
```
{
    "jsonColumn" : [
        {"data":{"a":"1","b":"2"},"timestamp":1719390721},
        {"data":{"a":"2","b":"4"},"timestamp":1719390722}
    ],
    "jsonColumn.timestamp": 1719390721,
    "jsonColumn.data": {"a":"1","b":"2"},
    "jsonColumn.data.a": 1,
    "jsonColumn.data.b": 2,
},
{
    "jsonColumn" : [
        {"data":{"a":"1","b":"2"},"timestamp":1719390721},
        {"data":{"a":"2","b":"4"},"timestamp":1719390722}
    ],
    "jsonColumn.timestamp": 1719390722,
    "jsonColumn.data": {"a":"2","b":"4"},
    "jsonColumn.data.a": 2,
    "jsonColumn.data.b": 4,
}
```

Added Kafka partition number to be available to schema metadata `__metadata$partition` when  `"stream.kafka.metadata.populate": "true"` in table config

Schema snippet:
```
{
"name": "__metadata$offset",
    ...
},
{
"name": "__metadata$partition",
    ...
},
```
 
Related documentation: [PR 353](https://github.com/pinot-contrib/pinot-docs/pull/353) in pinot-docs repo.
